{{!--
  Hero Section Partial
  Renders the top-of-README hero block: optional logo, project name, tagline,
  badges, and a short description paragraph.

  Expected context:
    - projectName  {string}        Project name (required). Rendered as an H1 heading.
    - tagline      {string}        Short one-line subtitle shown beneath the heading.
    - logoPath     {string}        Relative path or URL to a logo image. When omitted
                                   the logo <p> block is skipped.
    - badgeUrls    {array|object}  Badge definitions. Each entry should have:
                                     imageUrl  {string}  Shield/badge image src
                                     linkUrl   {string}  Hyperlink target (optional)
                                     alt       {string}  Alt text for the badge image
                                   When omitted, no badges are rendered.
    - description  {string}        One-paragraph prose description of the project.
    - version      {string}        Current semver string (used if badgeUrls is empty
                                   and the build script wants to auto-generate a
                                   version badge — handled externally).

  Design notes:
    - The logo block uses a centered HTML <p> tag for GitHub Markdown compat.
    - Badges are rendered inline in a single paragraph for compact display.
    - The description line is rendered as a plain Markdown paragraph.
    - All blocks are individually conditional so projects with no logo or no
      badges render cleanly without extra blank lines.
--}}
{{#if logoPath}}
<p align="center">
  <img src="{{logoPath}}" alt="{{projectName}} logo" width="120">
</p>
{{/if}}

# {{projectName}}

{{#if tagline}}
{{tagline}}
{{/if}}

{{#if badgeUrls}}
{{#each badgeUrls}}{{#if linkUrl}}[![{{alt}}]({{imageUrl}})]({{linkUrl}}) {{else}}![{{alt}}]({{imageUrl}}) {{/if}}{{/each}}
{{/if}}

{{#if description}}
{{description}}
{{/if}}
